{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\" style=\"font-family:;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">The objectives of the class are: 1) Theory of economic growth, 2) Historical experience of economic growth in Japan, the four Asian tigers (South Korea, Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Singapore), China, and India, and 3) Analysis of</span></span></span><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> these Asian economies during this century. future growth prospects. </span></span><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">is to understand. </span></span></span><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">This course helps prepare students to participate actively in the global economy.</span></span></span><span lang=\"JA\"> </span><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\"></span></p>", "到達目標": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\" style=\"font-family:;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">To achieve these goals, students read the latest literature on economic growth in Asia, learn about economic theory and policy in lectures, and discuss the relative strengths and weaknesses of different perspectives in class. This course will improve your English reading, listening and speaking skills. Improve your economics vocabulary and improve your critical economic thinking skills.</span></span></span></p>", "特記事項": "【合併】Japanese and Asian Economies A（経済学部）/Japanese and Asian Economies A（国際学部）/Ｊａｐａｎｅｓｅ ａｎｄ Ａｓｉａｎ Ｅｃｏｎｏｍｉｅｓ Ａ　（経済学研究科前期）", "関連科目": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">International Economics A</span></span><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\" style=\"font-family:;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">・</span></span></span><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">B, Development Economics A</span></span><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\" style=\"font-family:;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">・</span></span></span><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">B, Labor Economics A</span></span><span lang=\"JA\" yu=\"yu\" mincho\",serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\"=\"mincho',serif;mso-ascii-font-family:calibri;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-font-family:calibri;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;'\" style=\"font-family:;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">・</span></span></span></p>", "授業の概要・背景": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">This course is geared for undergraduate students. We first learn the theory of economic growth. We study how Japan became the first non-Western country to become a first world country and why growth slowed down after 1990. We explore the similarities and differences with the Four Asian Tigers along with the 1997 Asian Financial Crisis. We examine Chinese economic growth after 1978 and its recent slowdown. And we look at the prospects for India and its economic reforms.</span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0224px;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Graduate students will be expected to write a term paper based on the course material. The term paper should at least consist of objectives, theoretical considerations, empirical considerations, policy considerations and concluding remarks followed by references.</span></span></span></p>", "授業方法": "<br /><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">The lectures will be in English and conducted face to face in a classroom. The lectures will be accompanied by PowerPoint slides. Copies of the slides will be made available. Questions and discussion will be encouraged. Discussion questions will be provided ahead of time. course readings are in English and will be provided to the class. There will be a midterm exam and a final exam administered in class. The exams will be closed book and closed notes.&nbsp;</span></span></p>", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span style=\"font-size:11.0224px;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">April 11 </span></span><span style=\"white-space:pre;\">\t</span><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Introduction</span></span></span>", "<span calibri\",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\"yu=\"calibri',sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:'yu\" mincho\";mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"mincho';mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'times\" new=\"new\" roman\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:ja;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa;\"=\"roman';mso-bidi-the